00:54:16,400 --> 00:54:20,860
פסוק, but okay, and therefore the principle, therefore it was not a

1091
00:54:20,860 --> 00:54:23,120
good redemption. So the upshot of this is not bad, we finished

1092
00:54:23,120 --> 00:54:25,640
the whole דף Daf in like seven minutes, that side of it.

1093
00:54:25,820 --> 00:54:29,560
The upshot of this is that if the stuff can be eaten,

1094
00:54:30,060 --> 00:54:32,380
then you're יוצא, yotzei, even if it can only be eaten by

1095
00:54:32,380 --> 00:54:34,540
כהנים Kohanim and there's some cases where I might have thought it's

1096
00:54:34,540 --> 00:54:37,520
problematic, you didn't add the חומש, chomesh, you beat the כהן Kohen

1097
00:54:37,520 --> 00:54:40,880
out, but nevertheless it's okay. And if it can't be eaten, you're

1098
00:54:40,880 --> 00:54:43,980
not יוצא, even if it only can't be eaten מדרבנן, mi-derabbanan, like

1099
00:54:43,980 --> 00:54:47,220
the Rabbinic טבל, Tevel, or even cases that there was a technical

1100
00:54:47,220 --> 00:54:50,360
reason why it's still forbidden, like you tried to redeem it on

1101
00:54:50,360 --> 00:54:53,520
the wrong types of things. Nevertheless, if at the end of the

1102
00:54:53,520 --> 00:54:55,980
day it can't be eaten, then you are not יוצא מצה yotzei

1103
00:54:55,980 --> 00:54:58,800
Matzah and we will continue to discuss why you're not יוצא מצה

1104
00:54:58,240 --> 00:54:59,360
yotzei Matzah if it can't be

1105
00:55:00,700 --> 00:55:03,687
eaten. If it's forbidden to be eaten, we'll discuss that then.

1106
00:55:03,687 --> 00:55:07,206
The משנה *Mishnah* says these are the things with which a person

1107
00:55:07,206 --> 00:55:10,725
is יוצא *yotze* their obligation on פסח *Pesach*: with חטים *chitim*, with

1108
00:55:10,725 --> 00:55:14,244
שעורים *se'orim*, with כוסמין *kusmin*, with שיבולת שועל *shibolet shual*, and with

1109
00:55:14,244 --> 00:55:17,764
שיפון *shiffon*. These are the חמשת מיני דגן *chameshet minei dagan*. The

1110
00:55:17,764 --> 00:55:21,283
גמרא *Gemara* explains that only things that can become חמץ *chametz* are

1111
00:55:21,283 --> 00:55:24,802
valid for מצה *matzah*. This is learned from a היקש *hekesh* in

1112
00:55:24,802 --> 00:55:28,322
the פסוק *pasuk* between מצה *matzah* and חמץ *chametz*. Therefore, אורז *orez*

1113
00:55:28,322 --> 00:55:31,841
and דוחן *dochan* are excluded because they don't reach the state of

1114
00:55:31,841 --> 00:55:35,360
חימוץ *chimutz*, but rather סירחון *sirachon*. רבי יוחנן בן נורי *Rabbi Yochanan

1115
00:55:35,360 --> 00:55:38,880
ben Nuri* says אורז *orez* is a species of דגן *dagan*, but

1116
00:55:38,880 --> 00:55:42,399
the חכמים *Chachamim* say it is not. We only use these species

1117
00:55:42,399 --> 00:55:45,038
to be יוצא *yotze* the מצוה *mitzvah* of מצה *matzah*.
